ce:section.ce:para:
Herein, nicotinic acid and folic acid were originally utilized as the precursors to synthesize fluorescent CDs through one-step hydrothermal method (Fig. 1
                     ), and their fluorescence of CDs showed the response to varied pH values, which provided the potential of sensing pH by these CDs. Significantly, the as-prepared CDs were proved to be equipped with the functional groups of –CONH2, –COOH and –OH, and thus the related interactions with NO2
                     − and AA were observed. In particular, adding nitrite solution into CDs caused their fluorescence quenching due to the static quenching effect. Additionally, the subsequent introduction of AA inhibited the fluorescence quenching caused by nitrite, thus resulting in their fluorescence of CDs recovered.
